[{"id":"FT4116","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n<img alt=\"The figure consists of three spheres and their charges arranged horizontally with a vertical thread connected to the top of each sphere. The sphere on the left is labeled S sub 1 and has a positive charge. The sphere in the middle is labeled S sub 2, and the sphere on the right is labeled S sub 3. Both are uncharged.\" maxwidth=\"200\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/a4cbbc8fda0a92778ce2d37615d49957/original.png\" width=\"200\">\n<p>Three identical conducting spheres, <em>S</em>1, <em>S</em>2, and <em>S</em>3, are supported by insulating thread, as shown above. Initially, sphere <em>S</em>1 has a net positive charge and the other two spheres are uncharged. Spheres <em>S</em>1 and <em>S</em>2 are brought into contact and then separated. Next, spheres <em>S</em>2 and <em>S</em>3 are brought into contact and then separated. Which of the following shows the signs of the final net charges on the spheres?</p>","choicesHtml":["<img alt=\"Each option consists of 3 spheres and their charges arranged horizontally. \nOption A. All three spheres have a positive charge\" height=\"31\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/82be543c63ddb4b2bc95924a636611f6/original.png\" width=\"100\">","<img alt=\"Option B. The sphere on the left has a positive charge. The spheres in the middle and on the right are uncharged\" height=\"33\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/b38cbee6af630c2f148c6934a2d66176/original.png\" width=\"100\">","<img alt=\"Option C. The spheres on the left and in the middle are uncharged. The sphere on the right has a positive charge \" height=\"46\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/12d0066b3fbc9aec294126d0720ac54b/original.png\" width=\"100\">","<img alt=\"Option D. The sphere on the left is uncharged. The spheres in the middle and on the right have a positive charge.\" height=\"46\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/62a2616b953e6a18e2fe8b2cfd6de91a/original.png\" width=\"100\">"],"answer":-1}]